snippet.textDisplay: I'm still able to work, as I work in the grocery store deli.  These doctors, nurses, and others  are to be commended.  I had a woman come in and order just four tiny slices of meat and cheese.  It broke my heart!  I gave her $20 and told her to go buy some groceries.  Not the first time, and won't be the last.  BTW:  I know you don't like Trump, but he just ordered several companies to make more medical supplies at more affordable prices, in spite of them telling him no.  I do understand he seems to bait the other parties, but they have used their constituents to make money, they have used our children as their "fountains of youth", and they have bern fleecing our country, for over a century!  It's time we had someone with less than stellar behavior expose why they are always so "professional"... It's to keep us from knowing what they're really up to!  They sugar-coated everything, to make it more palatable, and were destroying this country from within!  The blinders are coming off, and more and more people are waking up to it.  Our water was contaminated, our food was contaminated, even food that should have been healthy for us, was only making us more ill, meds making us more ill, our air was poisoned with chem trails, and China deliberately released this virus, to not only cull their own population, but the population of the world.  This was just another way of carrying out Agenda 21.  NWO plan to destroy the world, in order to take it over.  They were even creating weather disasters to make money!  Everything we have experienced was to make money!  God is in control, now. It will get better, soon.  It sucks we have to lose so many great people, but they'll be back, with new lives, new bodies, and or world will be better than ever.  Thank you, to all who have given their everything (even their own lives), to help others in this distressing and difficult time.  I wish I could do more, but I'm not a professional of any kind.  My heart goes out to all whom have been affected.

snippet.textDisplay:
My sister is a Medical Sterilization technician and she went back to College at age 60 because her body could no longer handle heavy lifting of patients at the Extended care. She’ll be 64 this year and was counting days to retirement. Now she will end her career in the scariest situation. I’m very proud of her!

My husband is an Industrial Electrical Supervisor. He’s worked outside in dangerous environments his whole adult life. He’s considered essential. He is going to be 67 this year. I’m very proud of him too!

I’m on home front caring for my families needs. Pregnant daughter is high risk and her husband staying with us, but in our B & B Suite.
Cooking for a friend who fell etc

And add the list of so many working so we can have groceries, cleaning products , garbage removed etc. Amazing!
